<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-22T21:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-22T21:36:00-05:00" n="930" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2856.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-22T20:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1912—8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Situation in Sinaloa is graver; entire Culiacan district has risen.
                            Consul reports Americans being mistreated and robbed and have applied to
                            the American consul at Mazatlan (Alger) asking when, in the absence of
                            protection by the Mexican Government, they can expect it from the
                            Government of the United States. Consul has been notified of the sending
                            of this telegram, and also instructed to advise Americans where possible
                            to remove to a place of safety. The American interests in this section
                            are very great in property, and I believe some energetic action
                            necessary.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>